Step 1: Identify the quick assets. These typically include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable. (Inventory is not included.)

Step 2: Sum the quick assets using their End_amount values:
 • Cash on Hand: 2,339,224.10 
 • Bank Deposits: 4,292,000.00 
 • Interest Receivable: 14,796.43 
 • Accounts Receivable: 2,902,136.39 
 Total Quick Assets = 2,339,224.10 + 4,292,000.00 + 14,796.43 + 2,902,136.39 = 9,548,156.92

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities at End_amount – given as Total Current Liabilities = 631,880.98

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 9,548,156.92 / 631,880.98 ≈ 15.11

Thus, the Quick Ratio is approximately 15.11.
